**What They Want from This Post:** Permission and inspiration. They want to see designs that feel genuinely them — not too costume-y, not too safe. They're looking for the design that makes them feel powerful, a little dangerous, and completely put together. They save multiple images and compare. They want to know which version of vampy matches their specific vibe.

**What Satisfies Them:** Rich, curated visual inspo with copy that makes them feel seen. Specificity wins — "this is the design for dark romance energy" lands harder than "here are some vampy nail ideas." They love when content acknowledges the year-round wearability of dark aesthetics without being defensive about it.

**What Frustrates Them:** Generic round-ups that just list colours. Halloween-only framing that makes the aesthetic feel costume-adjacent. No guidance on short nails (feels excluded). No consideration for skin tone. Tutorials that are either too basic ("just use red polish") or unrealistically complex.

